Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.50,0:01:52.67,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine four...WE GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.84,0:01:59.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ore tachi wa...koko made kitaze
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.84,0:01:59.84,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We...made it this far
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.84,0:02:02.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ore tachi wa iku...yume no arika e
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.84,0:02:02.76,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We go...to where the dream is
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:07.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,dare mo oitekanaize--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.76,0:02:07.69,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,We won’t left anyone behind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.69,0:02:10.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,nshin aru nomi sore ga chikai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.69,0:02:10.48,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep going forward, that’s our pledge
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:14.36,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,yume ga hajimatta ano hi kara
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:14.36,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the day that the dream began
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:18.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,mezasu mirai wa onaji--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:18.70,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,the future that I’m \Naiming at hasn’t changed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:21.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,tto dekinai tomarenai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.70,0:02:21.20,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t stand still, I can’t stop
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.20,0:02:25.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,kokoro no taiyou shizumanai
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.20,0:02:25.58,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,The sun of my heart will never set
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.58,0:02:28.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ichi, ni, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.58,0:02:28.37,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.75,0:02:32.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ichi, ni, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.75,0:02:32.54,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.71,0:02:40.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,ichi, ni, Sunshine yon...we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.71,0:02:40.09,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, Sunshine four...WE GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:44.47,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.18,0:02:44.47,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,WE GO!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.35,0:02:52.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the pirates who are \Nafter the One Piece...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.73,0:02:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...head for the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.19,0:02:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the second half of the Grand Line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, no one has ever fully explored it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.32,0:03:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,except for Gold Roger, King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.45,0:03:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The New World has ruined many \Npirates' dreams and ambitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.42,0:03:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Monkey D. Luffy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.13,0:03:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a boy whose body turned to rubber\N after he ate the Gum-Gum Fruit,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.34,0:03:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and his friends venture into that sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.09,0:03:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna become the King of the Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After surviving a fierce battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.77,0:03:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Straw Hats finally \Nentered the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.52,0:03:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the harshest sea ruled\N by the Four Emperors.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.27,0:03:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After receiving an emergency \Nsignal, they landed on Punk Hazard;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.82,0:03:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an island with two parts,\N one burning, the other frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.78,0:03:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A branch of the Navy - G-5 - led by Smoker
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.45,0:03:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,reached the island while \Nchasing after the Straw Hats
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.20,0:03:52.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and got into a fight with Trafalgar\N Law who appeared out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you! Do you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.54,0:03:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your help the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.84,0:04:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shambles!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.22,0:04:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did he just do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.60,0:04:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there is some mastermind behind Law
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.85,0:04:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and if "CC" are his initials,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I know who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.32,0:04:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is the former colleague of Dr.Vegapunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is a scientist named Caesar Clown!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.83,0:04:37.84,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"The Worst in the World!\NA Scientist of Terror - Caesar!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.59,0:04:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Caesar Clown?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.52,0:05:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I have something on my mind, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember correctly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there were a lot of child abduction \Ncases taking place around here recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Child abduction?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.08,0:05:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, I can't get used seeing\N you like that, Captain-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.01,0:05:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped! \NYou have to deal with it for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.68,0:05:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tashigi! What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't heard about \Nany child abductions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.35,0:05:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please button up, Smoker-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:40.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like how open that Captain-chan\N is but she's scary inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.27,0:05:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.94,0:05:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I know is accidents at sea \Nhappen frequently in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in fact, I was wondering why accidents \Ninvolving children are so prevalent here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.53,0:05:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, that's true, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.08,0:05:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I actually go to the \Ncommunication department often...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I don't have glasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I've heard the G-5 gets \Nmany child abduction reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.34,0:06:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when it appears in the \Nnewspaper, it's often labeled
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.34,0:06:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an accident at sea or the work of pirates...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.34,0:06:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,…or simply a child gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.60,0:06:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, it could be the \Nreporter's mistake but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.85,0:06:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I thought maybe it's \Npossible that they were really...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.86,0:06:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it hard to say, Tashigi?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.28,0:06:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you think,\Njust say it clearly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.54,0:06:39.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw a bunch of kids earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.33,0:06:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're thinking maybe there \Nreally have been many abductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.96,0:06:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you think the \Nkidnapper is on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.10,0:06:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,those news articles were false...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.44,0:07:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...meaning somebody in the G-5 covered\N up those child abduction cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.74,0:07:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.74,0:07:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it mean somebody among us \Nis working for the kidnapper?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.62,0:07:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.75,0:07:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Smo-san, don't insult us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.71,0:07:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we are a spoiled group in the Navy
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but we take pride in being Navy soldiers!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.43,0:07:35.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right! None of us is doing that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.27,0:07:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.52,0:07:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.03,0:07:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fools are not even worth suspecting!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.28,0:07:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, all of you guys, \Ndon't expect too much from the Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.99,0:08:00.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as it consists of a group of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.37,0:08:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there is no organization that is perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.96,0:08:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you assume too much,\N you'll miss the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.50,0:08:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be fooled by appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.81,0:08:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger, Captain-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.31,0:08:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind, fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.44,0:08:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm the Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.48,0:08:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.28,0:08:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got fooled by their appearances!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.20,0:08:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Smoker-san, I'm not so sure\N about my theory though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.16,0:08:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. \NWe'd better keep it in mind anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.37,0:08:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But since my heart and \Nbody are in Law's hands,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.62,0:08:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't leave this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One third of you should leave \Nhere by ship, to make a report.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.46,0:08:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Vice Admiral?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.63,0:08:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our warship's been destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.43,0:08:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I saw their ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.81,0:09:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.60,0:09:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah! I hadn't thought of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a bad person!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful! Before it gets too late,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try to take back my heart and body,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and reveal who's really behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:18.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}VEGAPUNK'S FORMER THIRD LABORATORY
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.12,0:09:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally got through to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.16,0:09:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.12,0:09:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have permission to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.71,0:09:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Straw Hats, G-5, and Foxfire Kin'emon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.25,0:09:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter who dies on this island,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.38,0:09:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Joker will make it look \Nlike an accident at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.59,0:09:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catch as many of them as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.05,0:09:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The more guinea pigs, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.39,0:09:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.22,0:09:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can just kill the ones \Nwho can't be taken with poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.98,0:09:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Law go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.44,0:09:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He left the room a few minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.15,0:09:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.65,0:09:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the enemies has a \N400 million berry bounty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't push yourself too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.91,0:10:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other members are in a broad \Nrange of 120 million to 50 berries each.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.83,0:10:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them are wanted pirates
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and their bounties are 800 \Nmillion 50 berries in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they have been inactive \Nover the past two years
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so their bounty hasn't moved up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.09,0:10:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They could be more powerful\N than the numbers show.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You always study hard, Monet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.60,0:10:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.10,0:10:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what happened to you? It's extremely \Ncold and you didn't wear a coat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.73,0:10:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were robbed by some pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.81,0:10:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, they took \NBoss Brownbeard with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help him!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.82,0:10:41.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh really? I'm sorry to hear that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:44.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about Brownbeard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.83,0:10:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get him back at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.70,0:10:48.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to the backroom now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.21,0:10:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.50,0:10:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We just made a new medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.04,0:10:57.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will warm up your body\N and heal your wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.63,0:10:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?! That'd be nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.80,0:11:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please help the others, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.05,0:11:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.39,0:11:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But first, you have to get treated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.68,0:11:10.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.02,0:11:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this, Usopp?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.82,0:11:18.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of super!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.74,0:11:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.53,0:11:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.45,0:11:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It spoils Nami-san's beauty!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.95,0:11:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut the crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.74,0:11:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We get confused if nothing is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.96,0:11:32.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brownbeard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.08,0:11:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm sure you heard that name before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.00,0:11:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was what I used to go by.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.88,0:11:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.01,0:11:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you kidding, you fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.80,0:11:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go away, brats!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.26,0:11:47.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to you? \NYou were clammed up a while ago\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.81,0:11:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but now you're talkative.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.98,0:11:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Law's gonna come to save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.98,0:12:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I despise pirates from your generation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but Law is an exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.20,0:12:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean our generation?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you know anything, fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.45,0:12:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleven rookies with \Nbounties over 100 million
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.87,0:12:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who arrived at Sabaody at \Nthe same time two years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.50,0:12:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,plus Blackbeard...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.33,0:12:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People call you twelve \N"the Worst Generation."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You twelve are troublemakers...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.51,0:12:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...who were born at the change of the era
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.14,0:12:27.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and hold the key to the future\N of this war-torn world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.76,0:12:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After Whitebeard died, you all came\N to the New World and raised havoc.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.27,0:12:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When something big happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:39.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was always somebody \Nfrom your generation involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.23,0:12:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blackbeard! Kid! Law! Drake! Hawkins!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.07,0:12:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Basil Hawkins was the one who\N shattered my pirate group.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.74,0:12:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost both of my legs and ended my \Ncareer as a pirate thanks to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.83,0:12:57.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My crew were annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.79,0:13:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fled for my life and arrived here...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...on Punk Hazard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.42,0:13:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what this place is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.89,0:13:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This place... This island...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.48,0:13:20.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...used to be a lush green \Ntreasure house of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.52,0:13:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing like that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.75,0:13:43.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it housed a laboratory
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.30,0:13:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of Dr.Vegapunk, a Government scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.55,0:13:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were experimenting with and \Ndeveloping weapons and chemicals here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.06,0:14:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead of going to prisons,\N they brought some prisoners here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.06,0:14:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and performed experiments on \Nthem like they were guinea pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.99,0:14:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But four years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.15,0:14:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vegapunk's chemical \Nweapon test went wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And two of the three \Nlaboratories exploded!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.89,0:14:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the remains of that laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.63,0:15:07.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}THE REMAINS OF VEGAPUNK'S FORMER\N FIRST AND SECOND LABORATORY
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.88,0:15:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So there was a huge explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why this place is a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.31,0:15:21.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The explosion belched intense\N heat and toxic substances,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.23,0:15:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and killed each and every \Nliving thing on the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.50,0:15:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in that critical situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.71,0:15:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Government left those\N guinea-pig prisoners
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and escaped from the island \Nthen shut it down completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.80,0:15:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The prisoners stayed \Nin the Third Laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.77,0:16:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the only building that remained intact,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.35,0:16:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sheltered themselves from the \Npoison gas that was all over the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.65,0:16:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even those who survived were \Nparalyzed mainly in their lower body
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of the nerve gas
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.03,0:16:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and lost hope in their future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.49,0:16:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.91,0:16:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a year later,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,our merciful Master came to the island!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.58,0:16:30.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He purified the gas all over the \Nisland with his special ability
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.84,0:16:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gave those prisoners who couldn't\N walk mechanical means to move
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and took them on as his lackeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.60,0:16:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.69,0:16:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I landed here a year later after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,two years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.42,0:17:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were still some toxic \Nsubstances left in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.84,0:17:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I felt nauseous when I breathed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.63,0:17:19.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I thought I had no energy\N left to live and this was the end...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.73,0:17:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw the prisoners who \Nlost their legs like I did
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.73,0:17:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.20,0:17:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His kindness saved my \Nlife as it did to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.58,0:17:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vegapunk was a devil because \Nhe paralyzed my comrade's legs
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.38,0:17:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but the Master was our \Nwarm-hearted savior!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.05,0:18:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master!!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.01,0:18:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then a few months ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.14,0:18:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the second savior--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.02,0:18:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trafalgar Law who had \Ngained the title of Warlord...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...came to the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.69,0:18:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using his special ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.40,0:18:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he gave those of us who \Ncouldn't walk as we wished, legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.53,0:18:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The legs of living animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought we would never walk again
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.79,0:18:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we couldn't stop crying from happiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.17,0:18:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a touching story!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.63,0:18:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the Tra-guy is a good guy as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.22,0:18:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He saved my life, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.59,0:18:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vegapunk is a horrible person!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.47,0:18:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why there were those \Nhalf-sheep people at the laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.43,0:18:50.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Centaurs and the bird woman, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It all makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:54.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But wait. What about the dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.27,0:18:57.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, did you see the dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.15,0:19:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an artificial being that \NVegapunk created to guard the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.82,0:19:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can adapt itself to \Nany kind of environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.79,0:19:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard some Celestial Dragon\Nliked it and named it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot the name but if \Nyou see it, you better run.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.21,0:19:15.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's extremely aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.42,0:19:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.59,0:19:17.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We already ate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.96,0:19:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, now you know who rules the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one wants to come near it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.22,0:19:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Punk Hazard is our Master's property now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rejoice!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.48,0:19:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Master is still doing research\N today for the future of mankind!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.48,0:19:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He needs only a few guinea \Npigs and you can become one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.90,0:19:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.04,0:19:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:19:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master! I can't breathe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.51,0:20:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.18,0:20:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...medicine is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.10,0:20:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.77,0:20:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get me out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.90,0:20:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.32,0:20:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you feel now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.82,0:20:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Feeling nauseous and coughing, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.08,0:20:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.16,0:20:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a headache?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.83,0:20:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.12,0:20:33.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Feels like it's gonna split open!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.08,0:20:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh-huh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.25,0:20:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? It wasn't Vegapunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.80,0:20:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Smo-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.51,0:20:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who caused that huge explosion?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.59,0:20:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who made the weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.35,0:20:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and\N let it go off accidentally...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.22,0:20:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...was Caesar Clown!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Caesar Clown was
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:20:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the second-in-command in the \Nscience department at that time
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.98,0:21:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but since he had an inhumane streak,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.73,0:21:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was always butting heads with Vegapunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.57,0:21:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.08,0:21:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Help me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.50,0:21:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are your eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.13,0:21:18.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.38,0:21:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... there is... a giant snake in the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.05,0:21:30.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.43,0:21:33.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, that's good. Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.57,0:21:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the accident happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.19,0:21:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vegapunk's name came up only \Nbecause he was a person in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.70,0:21:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.91,0:21:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it was a crime to develop a mass-killing\N weapon that belches poison gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.54,0:21:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And since it had been brought\N to light by the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.96,0:21:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Caesar got arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.37,0:22:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But with his formidable ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.59,0:22:03.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he managed to escape from a prison ship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.63,0:22:06.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had been missing ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.72,0:22:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Caesar is still doing \Nresearch on this island,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.06,0:22:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we must stop him now!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.77,0:22:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna do something horrible again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.27,0:22:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Not good."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another failure?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.49,0:22:30.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Failure?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.24,0:22:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch your tongue!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.87,0:22:41.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,1)}A FORMER GOVERNMENT SCIENTIST\NBOUNTY: 300 MILLION BERRIES MASTER CAESAR CLOWN
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.62,0:22:35.41,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,My experiments never fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.41,0:22:37.91,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Even what happened four years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.91,0:22:41.83,DefaultLow,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone talks nonsense as usual!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.13,0:22:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A failed experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.71,0:22:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I "killed" the whole \Nisland with the weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.01,0:22:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a failure, World Government!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.47,0:22:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm capable of killing more\N enemies than anyone else.
